There are four programmatic tracks to the Livelihoods and Economic Recovery Group: 
1.	Stabilizing employment through income generation and emergency job creation;
2.	Supporting livelihoods analysis and programming in conflict and disaster contexts; 
3.	Supporting post-crisis socio-economic recovery through the sustainable reintegration of former combatants, internally displaced persons (IDPs) and returning refugees (in close liaison with UNHCR); and 
4.	Enabling livelihoods, return and reintegration through improved national capacities for the control, management and destruction of land mines, cluster munitions, other explosive remnants of war.
